- Sun 25 Aug 2019
[Reuters (abridged, edited)]
https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-health-ebola-congo/congo-has-given-over-200000-people-merck-ebola-vaccine-government-idUKKCN1VF0IG?rpc=401&

Congo has given over 200 000 people Merck Ebola vaccine: government
---------------------
Congolese authorities and health workers vaccinated more than 200 000 people against Ebola in August 2019, the government said on Sun 25 Aug 2019, using a Merck vaccine they hope will help rein in the world's 2nd worst epidemic.

Figures released by the government's Ebola committee showed that 204 044 people had been inoculated since 8 Aug 2019. A total of 1980 people have so far died in this epidemic, of 2950 people suspected to have been infected, clinically confirmed cases are a little lower, at 2845.

The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) said on Wed [21 Aug 2019] it will fund the manufacturing of Merck & Co Inc's investigational Ebola vaccine called V920. Another vaccine by Johnson and Johnson is available, but authorities have yet to deploy it for fear of creating confusion among an already skeptical and sometimes hostile population.

"The only vaccine that has been used in this epidemic is (the one) ... manufactured by Merck," the committee statement said.

Ebola appears to be under control in the city of Goma in Congo, but it has flared in other parts of the country, where aid workers are combating insecurity and misinformation on social media.

